gghstats is a self-hosted GitHub traffic dashboard and CLI. It stores
repository traffic and clone statistics in SQLite and exposes a web UI
and JSON API.

Features:
- Dashboard and CLI for GitHub traffic insights
- Configurable via environment file (token, filters, bind address, paths)
- One-shot or daemon mode via gghstats serve; suitable for rc.d
- Static binary (CGO_ENABLED=0)

WWW: https://github.com/hrodrig/gghstats
